The <b>Tennessee Municipal League</b> (TML) is an association of the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../475/3306475.xml">
incorporated</link> cities and towns of <region wordnetid="108630985" confidence="0.8">
<administrative_district wordnetid="108491826" confidence="0.8">
<location wordnetid="100027167" confidence="0.8">
<district wordnetid="108552138" confidence="0.8">
<country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../395/30395.xml">
Tennessee</link></country>
</district>
</location>
</administrative_district>
</region>
, organized for mutual assistance and improvement. <p>

The organization's functions include: 
<list>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../934/48934.xml">
lobbying</link> the <legislature wordnetid="108163273" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../500/904500.xml">
Tennessee General Assembly</link></legislature>
 on behalf of municipal governments, </entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

operating the TML Risk Management Pool, a cooperative risk-sharing arrangement established to provide <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../589/1853589.xml">
liability insurance</link> coverage, and </entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

operating the Tennessee <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../082/163082.xml">
Municipal Bond</link> Fund, which assists local governments in obtaining funding for capital projects.</entry>
</list>
</p>

